<br>
I added a HTML version of the spreedsheet.  Was a pain because I had to open the xls in Word then remove some formating and Save As HTML.  ( if anyone cares <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br>
<br>
Then I discovered a few ommisions ( DoTs ) and removed a few worthless Utility spells that most classes had, but rarely if ever use...like bind sight and Voice Graft.<br>
<br>
Removed the Mage class as having CR &amp; MR &quot;Buffs&quot; since they have summons for those &quot;Buffs&quot;.<br>
<br>
I want it to be as accurate &amp; objective as possible.  If anyone else has any other ideas or corrections, please lemme know.<br>
<br>
My take on the data ( based on it so far ), is that the mage class is not an utility class.  Many of the &quot;Happy&quot; raid level mages seem to think we are. If you want utility, other classes are much better suited/designed for that role.  The mage class is totally not a Defensive class...I think we can all agree that Defensively and sans pet...Mages stink.  Offensively, Mages are pretty good though...if pet can be used.  <br>
