<br>
I know the mage class and the bard class.  I have some familiarity with all the rest, but not an expert.<br>
<br>
I considered maybe giving the less or never used spells half a point,  but....<br>
<br>
Necro's may not ever cast that spell, but they still have the capability.  Druid's generally think their Bear pet is cute,  mostly worthless, but there is bound to be a druid or two out there that finds Boo Boo to be a powerful pet.  Shaman use their pets a lot in exp groups to add some extra damage.  Maybe not all the time, but they do use those pets and they add &quot;value&quot; to the class.<br>
<br>
The main point here is:  They have the spell...it's either on or off...binary...<br>
<br>
Fear Animal is a powerful spell.  For a ranger or a druid it rules for solo exp via fear kiting.<br>
